investment_tools

This is the code to copy/paste into an R script or markdown file.

install.packages(c("stringr", "rvest", "lubridate", "xml2"))
library(stringr)
library(rvest)
library(xml2)
library(lubridate)
urlTables <- function(url, ...) {
    rvest_installed <- "rvest" %in% rownames(installed.packages())
    if(!rvest_installed) {
         return(print("Install rvest first"))
    }
    website <- read_html(url)
    list <- html_table(website, ...)
    list
}

# Used to shift vectors 
shift <- function (x, shift_by)  {
    stopifnot(is.numeric(shift_by))
    stopifnot(is.numeric(x))
    if (length(shift_by) > 1) 
        return(sapply(shift_by, shift, x = x))
    out <- NULL
    abs_shift_by = abs(shift_by)
    if (shift_by > 0) 
        out <- c(tail(x, -abs_shift_by), rep(NA, abs_shift_by))
    else if (shift_by < 0) 
        out <- c(rep(NA, abs_shift_by), head(x, -abs_shift_by))
    else out <- x
    out
}

# Returns first day of month in a vector of dates, 
# if by_year = TRUE, returns first day of year. 
first_day <- function (x = "Vector of Dates", by_year = FALSE) {
    x = as.Date(as.character(x))
    day = format(x, format = "%d")
    monthYr = format(x, format = "%Y-%m")
    y = tapply(day, monthYr, min)
    first = as.Date(paste(row.names(y), y, sep = "-"))
    if (by_year) {
         first = first[grepl("[[:digit:]]+-01-[[:digit:]]+", first)]
    }
    return(as.factor(first))
}


# Used to get divided data from various sources
div_data <- function(ticker, NASDAQ=FALSE, DIVIDATA = FALSE,...) {
    rvest_installed <- "rvest" %in% rownames(installed.packages())
    if(!rvest_installed) {
         return(print("Install rvest first"))
    }
    if (NASDAQ) {
        website <- xml2::read_html(paste0("http://www.nasdaq.com/symbol/",
                                          ticker, "/dividend-history"))
        list <- rvest::html_table(website, ...)
        list <- list[[6]]
        col_names <- sub(" ", "", names(list))
        col_names[1] <- "ExEffDate"
        names(list) <- col_names
        list$ExEffDate <- as.Date(list$ExEffDate, "%m/%d/%Y")
        list$DeclarationDate <- as.Date(list$DeclarationDate, "%m/%d/%Y")
        list$RecordDate <- as.Date(list$RecordDate, "%m/%d/%Y")
        list$PaymentDate <- as.Date(list$PaymentDate, "%m/%d/%Y")
        return(list)
    }
    if(DIVIDATA) {
        website <- xml2::read_html(paste0("https://dividata.com/stock/",
                                          ticker,"/dividend"))
        list <- rvest::html_table(website, ...)
        exDivDate <- list[[1]][,1]
        dividend <- list[[1]][,2]
        exDivDate <- as.Date(exDivDate, format = "%B %d, %Y")
        dividend <- sub("\\$", "", dividend)
        data.frame(Date = exDivDate, ex_dividend = as.numeric(dividend))
    }
    website <- read.csv(
               paste0("http://chart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s=",ticker
                      ,"&a=0&b=2&c=1962&d=0&e=26&f=2017&g=v&ignore=.csv")
               )
    website$Date <- as.Date(website$Date)
    website
}
stock_quote <- function (stockName = "vector of tickers", year = 1900, day = 1, month = 1)  {
    lubridate_installed <- "lubridate" %in% rownames(installed.packages())
    if(!lubridate_installed) {
         return(print("First, install the package 'lubridate'."))
    }
    returnIt <- list(NA)
    if (missing(year)) {
        year <- 1000
    }
    returnList <- list(NA)
    cur_date <- Sys.Date()
    cur_year <- format(cur_date, "%Y")
    cur_month <- format(cur_date, "%m")
    cur_day <- format(cur_date, "%d")

    for (i in 1:length(stockName)) {
        url <- paste0("http://chart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s=",stockName[i], 
                      "&a=", month-1, "&b=", day, "&c=", year, "&d=", cur_month, 
                      "&e=",cur_day,"&f=", cur_year,"&g=d&ignore=.csv")
        
        # Cleaning up by day data.
        byDay <- read.csv(url)
        byDay$Date <- as.Date(byDay$Date)
        byDay <- subset(byDay, Date > as.Date(paste0(year, "-01-01")))
        byDay$Date <- as.Date(byDay$Date)
        
        # Get dividends
        divs <- div_data(stockName[i])
        
        byDay = merge.data.frame(divs, byDay, by="Date", all.y = TRUE)
        byDay[is.na(byDay)] = 0
        #return(divs)aap
        # Cleaning up by week
        byWeek <- subset(byDay, lubridate::wday(byDay$Date) == 2)
        rownames(byWeek) <- NULL
        
        # Cleaning up by month
        byMonth <- data.frame(Date = as.Date(first_day(byDay$Date)))
        byMonth <- merge(byDay, byMonth)
        byMonth <- byMonth[order(byMonth$Date, decreasing = TRUE), ]
        rownames(byMonth) <- NULL
        
        # Cleaning up by year
        byYear <- data.frame(Date = as.Date(first_day(byDay$Date, by_year = TRUE)))
        byYear <- merge(byYear, byDay)
        byYear <- byYear[order(byYear$Date, decreasing = TRUE), ]
        rownames(byYear) <- NULL
        
                byDay <- byDay[order(byDay$Date, decreasing = TRUE), ]
        
        byDay$Percent.Change <- (byDay$Close - shift(byDay$Close, 1))/shift(byDay$Close, 1) * 100
        byDay$Ri <- log((byDay$Close + byDay$Dividends)/shift(byDay$Close, 1))
        byDay$WriM1 <- exp(byDay$Ri)-1
        byDay$logRet <- cumsum(byDay$WriM1)
        byMonth$Percent.Change <- (byMonth$Close - shift(byMonth$Close, 1))/shift(byMonth$Close, 1) * 100
        byYear$Percent.Change <- (byYear$Close - shift(byYear$Close, 1))/shift(byYear$Close, 1) * 100
        byWeek$Percent.Change <- (byWeek$Close - shift(byWeek$Close, 1))/shift(byWeek$Close, 1) * 100
        
        
        returnList$byDay <- byDay
        returnList$byMonth <- byMonth
        returnList$byYear <- byYear
        returnList$byWeek <- byWeek
        returnIt[[stockName[i]]] <- returnList
        returnIt[[stockName[i]]] <- returnIt[[stockName[i]]][-1]
    }
    returnIt <- returnIt[-1]
    return(returnIt)
}

Create a vector with the stock tickers you wish to lookup.

tickers <- c("SPY", "AKRX", "GE", "GLD", "TIP", "GOOG", "AKAM", "SIFY")

Next, use the stock_quote() function to get the information desired. You can select a specific date by using the arguments year = whatever, day = whatever, month = whatever. If you do not select year, day, or month the function will default to the oldest possible date.
